    "summary": "THOMAS HERRMANN\nwas born in Karlsruhe in 1973. He studied at the University of Paderborn by Marton Ke\u00f6nch, at the Academy of Art in Darmstadt by Prof. Grigory Gruzman, at the Hochschule f\u00fcr Musik Detmold by Prof. Anatol Ugorsky and at the Conservatory of Amsterdam by Prof. Naum Grubert, where he got his solo-degree with magna cum laude.\n\nRecitals and chamber music concerts have taken Thomas Herrmann to many countries throughout Europe, China, Morocco and to South Africa.\nHe also performed at numerous festivals; e.g. at the \u201eGergiev Festival\u201c, at the \u201eChopinfestival\u201c in Bergen at the \u201eRussian Chambermusicfestival\u201c in Gent.\nThomas Herrmann plays regularly as a soloist with various orchestras in Germany, made TV-recordings for the German ZDF,the National Chinese TV and played for recordings of the Netherlands Broadcasting Co. in the Concertgebouw of Amsterdam.\n\nSince 1999 Thomas Herrmann gives regularly masterclasses at the Conservatory of Potchefstroom in South Africa. \n\nSince the year 2003 he also gives each year masterclasses for chamber music at the Summer academy of Friedrichsdorf.\n\nSince the year 2010 Thomas Herrmann has his own piano-course in AROSA (Zwitserland).\n\nFrom 2014 - 2018 he was Head Music, Dance and Theater and member of the management team of the Music- and Danceschool in Amstelveen.\n\nSince 2018 he is lecturer for piano  at the Royal Conservatoire of The Hague\n\nSpecialties: CD's published:\n\n1998: Thomas Herrmann live! Solo-CD with live-recordings of Mozart (pianoconcert) and Schumann \n\n2001:CD with the Erasmus Trio and the violinist Vera Laporeva\n\n2002:Solo-CD with works from Scarlatti, Beethoven, Brahms, Bartok and Sch\u00f6nberg\n\n2007:CD with the Erasmus Trio \u201cMusical Gems\u201d (Bloomline) \n\n2007:CD with his piano-duo \u201cDiversity\u201d (Flexaton)\n\n2017: CD duo with Vera Laporeva  with works by George Sosnovski\n\n2021: Lees- & luisterboek 'De avonturen van een rossig jongetje' van Vera Laporeva \n\nFrom 2006 - 2017 Thomas Herrmann was artistic director of the International Chamber Music Festival of the Haarlemmermeer.",
